equation_narrative.headline: Hydrophobic core context drives confident leucine prediction from early layers
equation_narrative.story: Position 8 in ubiquitin sits in a hydrophobic core environment, receiving strong structural contact signals from buried aliphatic residues. The representation assembles this hydrophobic character through layers 1-23, with the logit lens consistently projecting toward branched aliphatic residues (L, V, I). The decision phase (L24-33) sees leucine-specific prediction channels activate decisively: MLP neurons at L30-32 cast strong votes for L, and by L33, the final MLP layer drives confidence to 99.51% through highly L-enriched features. The model's perception of the hydrophobic burial context perfectly aligns with the correct answer.

perception_phase.summary: Layers 1-23 assemble a representation of position 8's hydrophobic burial context. Three structural contacts and three co-evolving positions provide input, though attention heads show relatively modest structural reading (L19:H17 erases with -2.28 projection via local attention). Early features encode general sequence context (F1:5480, F1:9146 with ~45 projection), while mid-layer features at L9 maintain hydrophobic character (F9:5728 with 51.26 projection). The logit lens shows frequent lead changes between hydrophobic residues (L, V, I, F) and occasional polar intrusions (S peaks at 22.6% at L0, K briefly leads at L8), reflecting the model's exploration of compatible chemistries. By L23, the representation stabilizes with L at 25%, V at 12%, and I at 15%, consistent with a buried aliphatic environment.
perception_phase.context_character: The assembled context is strongly hydrophobic and buried: three structural contacts, flanked by hydrophobic residues (I, F, V, K in local sequence), with co-evolutionary signal from three positions. The representation character through L23 is consistently aliphatic-leaning, though the logit lens explores various hydrophobic options.
key_information_sources: Structural contacts: 3 residues providing hydrophobic burial signal
Co-evolutionary coupling: 3 positions suggesting functional constraints on this site
Local sequence: IFVKT[L]TGKTI — hydrophobic neighbors (I7, F5, V6) dominate immediate context
L9 attention features: F9:5728 (51.26 proj), F9:1281 (47.27 proj) encode mid-layer hydrophobic representation
L18 features: F18:7824 (6.82 proj), F18:312 (6.75 proj) maintain modest hydrophobic signal into late perception

decision_phase.summary: The decision crystallizes between L24-33 as leucine-specific prediction channels activate. L24 sees the first strong MLP commitment (N24:2104 projects 0.485 toward L), and L25 amplifies this with multiple L-specific writers (N25:235 at 0.566, N25:1424 at 0.484). L30-32 deliver the decisive push: N30:2914 projects 0.995 toward L, and L32's MLP layer contributes a massive +16.75 total projection. The final layer (L33) features dominate with extreme L-specificity: F33:1406 (132.14 proj), F33:8356 (128.66 proj), driving confidence from 87% to 99.51%.
decision_phase.transition: The L23-25 boundary marks the shift from perception to decision. At L23, the representation remains multi-candidate (L 25%, I 15%, V 12%) with net negative MLP contribution (-1.61). L24 sees the first decisive MLP commitment (+1.14 total projection, led by N24:2104's L-specific vote), and L25 amplifies with +3.66 MLP projection. AA-specific prediction features emerge at L24 (F24:10033, F24:9164 with 17+ projection) and intensify through L30-33.

candidates.narrative: Leucine emerges as the clear winner through sustained MLP support in the decision phase. After hovering around 10-25% through L23, L jumps to 44.6% by L29 as prediction neurons activate (N27:3857, N28:3236, N29:3215 all contribute). The decisive surge occurs L30-33: N30:2914 projects 0.995, N31:1117 adds 0.582, and L32's massive MLP layer (+16.75 total) includes strong L-specific writers (N32:2581 at 1.035, N32:875 at 0.927). L33 features with extreme enrichment (F33:1406 at 132.14 proj, F33:8356 at 128.66) finalize the 99.51% confidence.
candidates.key_layers: Steady through L23 (25%), decisive surge L27-33 (44.6% → 99.51%)
key_evidence: N30:2914 (0.995 proj) — strong L-specific vote in late decision phase
N32:2581 (1.035 proj), N32:875 (0.927 proj) — L32 MLP layer delivers +16.75 total
F33:1406 (132.14 proj), F33:8356 (128.66 proj) — final layer features with extreme L-specificity

candidates.narrative: Isoleucine competes through mid-decision layers but loses decisively. I rises from 1.2% at L0 to peak at 18.82% at L27, supported by hydrophobic context overlap with L. However, I-specific prediction channels fail to activate: while L gains strong MLP support at L30-32, I receives net negative contributions. By L33, I collapses to 0.24% as the final layer's L-enriched features (F33:1406, F33:8356) overwhelm any I signal.
key_evidence: Peak at L27 (18.82%) reflects hydrophobic representation compatibility
Lacks dedicated prediction neurons in L30-33 decision phase
Final layer features show no I-specific enrichment

candidates.narrative: Valine's prominence in the logit lens (peaks 22% at L19) reflects the representation's exploration of small branched aliphatic residues during perception. V leads briefly at L16-21, consistent with the hydrophobic burial context being assembled. However, this is representation character, not prediction: V lacks dedicated prediction channels in the decision phase. V-specific erasers dominate L26-29 (N26:1978 projects -0.648 against L), and by L33, V settles at 0.05%.
candidates.key_layers: Peaks L19 (22%), leads L16-21, fades L24+ (→0.05%)
key_evidence: L16-21 prominence reflects hydrophobic representation character, not model belief
N26:1978 (-0.648 proj) erases V in favor of L during decision phase
No V-specific prediction features activate at L30-33

candidates.narrative: Serine's 22.6% probability at L0 is an embedding artifact, not a meaningful signal. S represents polar chemistry incompatible with the hydrophobic burial context. The representation quickly suppresses S: it drops to 5% by L8 and remains below 10% through L29. S lacks any prediction channel support in the decision phase and collapses to 0.06% by L33. Its early logit-lens prominence reflects the model's initial uncertainty before structural and co-evolutionary context arrives.
candidates.key_layers: Peaks L0 (22.6%), suppressed by L8 (5%), irrelevant by L24+
key_evidence: L0 peak is embedding artifact before context assembly
Incompatible with hydrophobic burial context assembled L1-23
No polar-supporting features activate in decision phase

turning_points.description: The representation transitions from embedding initialization to hydrophobic context encoding. S's initial 22.6% drops as structural and local sequence information flows in. Multiple lead changes (S→Y→H→L→F) reflect the model's exploration of compatible chemistries. By L9, the representation stabilizes around branched aliphatic residues (L, V, I, F), consistent with the buried hydrophobic environment being read from structural contacts and local sequence (IFVKT context).

The perception-to-decision transition occurs here. L23 shows multi-candidate representation (L 25%, I 15%, V 12%) with net negative MLP activity (-1.61). L24 marks the first decisive MLP commitment: N24:2104 projects 0.485 toward L, and total MLP contribution flips to +1.14. L25 amplifies with +3.66 MLP projection (N25:235 at 0.566, N25:1424 at 0.484). By L27, L reaches 44.6% while I peaks at 18.82%, setting up the final resolution.

The final commitment phase delivers overwhelming L-specificity. L30 MLP neurons cast strong L votes (N30:2914 at 0.995, N30:1786 at 0.812) despite net negative total (-2.46, due to competing erasers). L32 provides the decisive surge: +16.75 total MLP projection, led by N32:2581 (1.035), N32:875 (0.927), N32:1175 (0.918). L33's massive MLP delta (+16.79) activates extreme L-enriched features (F33:1406 at 132.14, F33:8356 at 128.66), driving confidence from 87% to 99.51%.

deep_dives.label: Early context assembly (L1, L9)
deep_dives.caption: L1 features encode initial sequence context (F1:5480, F1:9146, F1:1508 all ~45 proj). L9 features maintain hydrophobic representation (F9:5728 at 51.26, F9:1281 at 47.27) as structural information integrates. These encode 'what's here' not 'what should be here.'

deep_dives.label: Mid-layer representation (L18)
deep_dives.caption: L18 features show modest projections (F18:7824 at 6.82, F18:312 at 6.75), reflecting the representation's stabilization around hydrophobic character before the decision phase begins. The low magnitude indicates context assembly is nearly complete.

deep_dives.label: Decision onset (L24)
deep_dives.caption: L24 marks the first appearance of high-projection features (F24:10033 at 17.05, F24:9164 at 16.65), signaling the shift from perception to prediction. These attention-stream features begin to encode AA-specific preferences.

deep_dives.label: MLP decision layers (L24-27)
deep_dives.caption: L24-27 show the MLP's commitment to L. N24:2104 (0.485 proj), N25:235 (0.566), N25:1424 (0.484), N27:3857 (0.425) cast increasingly confident L votes. Total MLP projection rises from +1.14 (L24) to +2.06 (L27).

deep_dives.label: Final MLP surge (L30-32)
deep_dives.caption: L30-32 deliver the decisive L commitment. N30:2914 (0.995), N31:1117 (0.582), and especially L32's massive layer (+16.75 total, led by N32:2581 at 1.035, N32:875 at 0.927) drive L from 44.6% to 87%.

deep_dives.label: Final layer features (L33)
deep_dives.caption: L33 features show extreme L-specificity: F33:1406 (132.14 proj), F33:8356 (128.66), F33:2789 (128.1). These MLP-stream features represent the model's final prediction channels, driving confidence to 99.51%.

deep_dives.label: Key attention heads
deep_dives.caption: L19:H17 erases with -2.28 projection via local attention. L30:H19 writes +2.82 via local attention (84% local attn weight). L31:H17 erases -3.20 via co-evolutionary reading (10% coevol attn). These heads shape the representation's evolution.

equation_narrative.resolution: The model correctly predicts leucine with 99.51% confidence by assembling a hydrophobic burial context through layers 1-23, then activating L-specific prediction channels in layers 24-33. The decisive evidence comes from L30-33 MLP neurons (N30:2914, N32:2581, N32:875) and final-layer features (F33:1406, F33:8356) that encode extreme L-specificity. The three structural contacts, three co-evolving positions, and local hydrophobic sequence (IFVKT) all support leucine as the optimal residue for this buried core position in ubiquitin.
